SQL Single Row Functions Practise Questions
[1/19/2026]
You are given the following string:

'  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**'

-Find the length of the string.
select '  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**' as Str,
length('  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**') as "Length of string"
from dual;

-Remove the leading and trailing spaces.
select '  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**' as Str,
LTRIM( '  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**', 'H') as LTRIMMED,
RTRIM('  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**','*') as RTRIMMED
from dual;

Remove the * and . characters from the ends of the string.
select '  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**' as Str,
REGEXP_REPLACE('  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**', '[.*]', '') as replaced
from dual;


Find the position of @ in the string.
select '  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**' as Str,
instr('  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**','@') as "Position of @"
from dual;

Extract the substring from position 5 to 10.



Pad the string to length 30 with # on the left.
select '  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**' as Str,
LPAD('  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**',30,'%')
FROM DUAL;


Pad the string to length 30 with * on the right.

select '  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**' as Str,
RPAD('  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**',30,'%')
FROM DUAL;

Remove all special characters (anything that is not a letter or number) using regex
select '  Hel#lo! H@rri$.**' as Str,



